  "texts": [
    "A is said to provide 𝜖𝑑 X -privacy if and only if for any two input data 𝑥, 𝑥 ∈ X and for any possible output 𝑦 ∈ Y satisfied:𝑃𝑟 (A (𝑥) = 𝑦) 𝑃𝑟 (A ( 𝑥) = 𝑦) ≤ 𝑒𝑥𝑝 (𝜖𝑑 X (𝑥, 𝑥))(6)where 𝑑 X is a distance function defined on X and 𝜖 is the privacy parameter that controls the privacy protection strength.",
    "Note that same as differential privacy, 𝑑 X -privacy also has the post-processing property [4].",
    "That is to say, if A satisfied 𝑑 X -privacy, then for any deterministic or randomized algorithm A ′, A • A ′ satisfies 𝑑 X -privacy.",
    "Implementation of 𝑑 X -privacy.",
    "In FELLAS, users' interacted items are the most important privacy protection objective, therefore, we replace each item in user sequence using 𝑑 X -privacy mechanism."
  ],
